**Abstract:**
Essay fragment dated July 29, 1991, titled "The God of Philosophers and the God of Faith." The document begins by acknowledging the radical difference sensed since Pascal's time between the philosophical God and the God of Christian faith. It argues that this separation became institutionalized in the thirteenth century when Christian thinkers encountered Aristotle's works and began understanding faith in Aristotelian categories. The fragment connects this to Frei's analysis of the eclipse of biblical narrative.

**AI Recommendation:** Early essay fragment on central theme of God-of-philosophers distinction; shows early formulation of Chantilly project themes.

